init_text:
Is Listening to a Book Just as Good as Reading It?

Do you listen to audiobooks? What are the benefits, in your opinion, of listening instead of reading? Are there advantages to reading that cannot be gained by listening? Which method do you prefer? Why?

---

In my opinion,

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: One is that I can listen to an audiobook while driving or doing other hands-free activities, such as cleaning the house or doing chores.

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: In fact, I've been able to knit with both hands while listening to an audiobook; I'm sure that there are many people who would never

actions.name: text-insert
actions.text: Another benefit is that people can listen to audiobooks at night when the lights are down.
